1. Install Prerequisites
JDK Setup (for Java-based integration):

Download and install the latest Java Development Kit (JDK) from Oracle or use OpenJDK (sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk for Linux).
Verify installation:
bash
Copy code
java -version
javac -version
Python Setup:

Install Python 3.10+ from Python.org.
Install pip for package management (sudo apt install python3-pip for Linux).
Verify installation:
bash
Copy code
python --version
pip --version
IDK Setup:

Integrated Development Kit (IDK) usually refers to IDE tooling like IntelliJ IDEA for Java or PyCharm for Python. Download PyCharm or use VS Code with Python extensions.
